Six people were killed and two injured on Saturday during clashes between two clans over a disputed boundary in Wajir county.Police said the fight involved members of the neighbouring Jibril and Matan clans.It took place in Baghala area when a group of Matan men invaded the Jibril, whom they found waiting.A shootout ensued forcing some of them to retreat.Police launched investigations with the aim of confiscating weapons, which the locals possess illegally.Officers were deployed to keep the peace.Read: MP urges state to end Wajir clan hostilitiesAlso read: Uhuru orders Mandera, Wajir to surrender illegal arms